{"sections":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides components ready to be used, specified in Figma assets and preventing users to handle tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They are rendered thanks to the theme in use.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26.4","projectFiles":"OUDS-Discovery-Tutorial.zip","chapter":"Use of first components provided by OUDS","image":"ic_component_intro.png","estimatedTimeInMinutes":30,"title":"Use your first OUDS components","backgroundImage":"ic_component_intro.png","kind":"hero"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We will work on a kind of formular using main OUDS components.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Feel free to style and design things as you want.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia"}],"stepsSection":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"First, prepare the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ContentView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" by adding inside it a ","type":"text"},{"code":"ScrollView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","media":null,"caption":[],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-1.swift"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Now, let’s add radio buttons to let the user choose its gender.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The official components are ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSRadio","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSRadioItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but the package has also a ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSRadioPicker","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to implement quicky a group of radios.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This component can be replaced by your own.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The radio picker is defined by an array of values to display radio items associated to a tag, i.e. an ","type":"text"},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" thing shared through a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Binding","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Inside a picker the user can select only one value, not zero.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-2.png","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add such picker with three items inside.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-2.swift"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The radio picker is alone, it is the time to add below a checkbox. OUDS provides two components: ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckbox","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which is a simple checkbox, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which is a checkbox (duh!) with additional texts and icons.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The state of the checkbox is shared through a boolean ","type":"text"},{"code":"State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In some cases you may need to use ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxIndeterminate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if you want a three-states checkbox.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-3.png","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a checkbox item with only two states."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-3.swift"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are also components who do not have any behaviors and are here only for visual rendering, for example dividers which can be horizontal or vertical."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A divider is, in the end, a stroke with a color. You will see later, colors in OUDS have two values: a light mode value, and a dark mode value. Here the divider can have a color which can change, or not."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-4.png","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Choose to add an instance of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-4.swift"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With radio and checkbox, OUDS provides also switch elements (toggles). They can be alone ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwitch"},{"type":"text","text":") or with texts ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwitchItem"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Just like the checkbox, the switch exposes its state through a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-5.png","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a switch item, it will be used as a trick to force the change of the color scheme for the view for our future operations.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You will then be able to see the automatic changes of colors when you switch the color scheme.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-5.swift"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Users may need to navigate outside the app, like, for example, opening a website. Thus the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSLink"},{"text":" component can be integrated. It can be only with a text or also a chevron indicator.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-6.png","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSLink"},{"text":" in the app and make it open the iOS documentation OUDS website.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-6.swift"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the end, we can also add a button. Button are one of the most used components in an app and bring a lof of the power and the style of the brand."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can find it with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton"},{"text":". Such button has an appearance changing its colors, and also a style (loading or not).","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Thanks to the theme, the enabled, disabled, hover, focus or pressed states are managed.","type":"text"}]}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-7.png","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s add a button with some rules: if checkbox is not checked it is disabled. When tapped, change the style of the button during 5 seconds.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-7.swift"}],"anchor":"Add-basic-components","title":"Add basic components"}]},{"assessments":[{"type":"multiple-choice","content":[],"choices":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No! The components use the design specifications, i.e. tokens, thanks to the theme, to define the style they must have in all cases."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"No","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the reason why the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":" is so important: it injects the theme as environment variable so that any component can get it to define its style."}]}]}],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Does the developer using OUDS component need to manage the look and feel of the components?"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"assessments","anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding"},{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Components can be similar to iOS native components, or can also be original and strongly related to Orange Unified Design System needs."}],"kind":"callToAction","featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","action":{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"overridingTitle":"Get started"},"title":"Add more OUDS components"}],"kind":"project","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"category":"Orange Unified Design System","title":"Use your first OUDS components","categoryPathComponent":"Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)","role":"project"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)","paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/$volume","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS"]],"modules":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}]}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSTh